Fire has razed goods worth millions of naira as 24 shops were burnt in Muda Lawal Market, Bauchi State The Public Relations Officer of the Bauchi State Fire Service, Muhammad T Bature who confirmed the incident said that the incident happened on Friday afternoon. He added that Fire Service personnel mobilized to the scene with five fire fighting trucks. He said investigation was still on to ascertain the damages or loss incurred in the incident. Meanwhile, traders alleged that black marketers operating at Muda Lawal Market, Bauchi, caused the inferno which razed down shops and part of Jummaat Mosque. The fire incident lasted for over one and half hour, before men of the Fire Service quenched it.